aVThree of the nation's leading military contractors -- the General Dynamics Corporation, the Northrop Grumman Corporation and the McDonnell Douglas Corporation -- reported improved first-quarter profits yesterday, despite cuts in military spending. "Generally the numbers are quite good," said Wolfgang Demisch, an analyst at BT Securities. He noted that McDonnell Douglas had exceeded Wall Street's expectations, reporting strong results in its military aircraft sector.
