VThe Northrop Grumman Corporation said yesterday that it would lay off 1,100 employees at its military aircraft division as a result of the cancellation of an Air Force attack missile program. The Los Angeles-based company will begin issuing 60-day layoff notices to employees at the division in Hawthorne, Calif. The Air Force canceled the missile program for budgetary reasons, the company said.
