VThe Goodrich Corporation said yesterday that the Northrop Grumman Corporation would pay it $99 million to settle claims related to its 2002 purchase of Northrop's aeronautical-systems business. Goodrich, based in Charlotte, N.C., said the settlement covered customer warranty issues and other contract claims for products made by Northrop's TRW Aeronautical Systems unit. Northrop, based in Los Angeles, has already made a $10 million deposit and was expected to pay the remaining $89 million by the end of this month. Goodrich said it had assumed some future liabilities as part of the agreement and that it would record pretax costs of $20 million to $30 million, or 11 cents to 17 cents a share, in the current quarter for those possible future claims.
