aVThe Justice Department filed suit today to block the Lockheed Martin Corporation's planned acquisition of the Northrop Grumman Corporation, contending that a combination of these two leading military contractors posed a threat to the nation's defense. ''This merger isn't just about dollars and cents,'' Attorney General Janet Reno said in announcing the litigation. ''It's about winning wars and saving lives.'' The proposed merger, Ms. Reno added, would ''cost taxpayers more and take the competitive wind out of the sails of innovation in the production of many critical systems that protect our fighting men and women.''
