aVEarly last week, Frank C. Lanza, the chief executive of L-3 Communications, an aerospace and communications company in New York, received a not-too-surprising telephone call from military officials. ''They asked us, 'Can you do the following things, and how long will it take you to do it,' '' Mr. Lanza said. ''They are in the planning process. And they need to know about our ability to deliver certain products.''
