VThe Northrop Grumman Corporation is suing the Lockheed Martin Corporation over accusations that Lockheed cut it out of a $4 billion Army contract, escalating a fight among various companies over the shrinking number of military contracts. Northrop's lawsuit, filed in Federal District Court in San Jose in December, states that after Northrop helped Lockheed secure a contract to manufacture a new missile defense system, Lockheed assigned Northrop's share of the job to one of its own production units.
