aV1st-Quarter G.D.P. Rose At a Sluggish 1.3% Pace For the first time since 1995, the economy grew by less than 2 percent for two consecutive quarters, the government reported. The gross domestic product, a measure of the output of goods and services, rose at an annual pace of 1.3 percent in the first quarter, slower than the 2 percent expected but up from the 1 percent pace in the fourth quarter. [C3.]
