aVThe military contractor General Dynamics Corporation said yesterday that it had extended its tender offer for shares of Newport News Shipbuilding Inc. again as it waits for a government decision on the proposed merger. General Dynamics, which is battling a rival, the Northrop Grumman Corporation, to take over Newport News, extended its offer to Aug. 3. It had been scheduled to expire on July 20. About 21.2 million Newport News shares had been tendered to General Dynamics as of July 20, far exceeding the majority of shares outstanding, the company said. Last week Northrop extended its offer for Newport News to Aug. 2 and said about 2.26 million shares had been tendered. The acquisition proposals from General Dynamics and Northrop are under regulatory review by the Justice and Defense Departments.
