VThe Northrop Grumman Corporation announced an unsolicited $5.9 billion stock offer today for the TRW Corporation in the hope of becoming the nation's leading satellite and missile contractor as military spending rises in response to terrorist threats. Northrop's chairman, Kent Kresa, sent a letter on Thursday to Philip A. Odeen, TRW's nonexecutive chairman, and Kenneth W. Freeman, a board member, offering shareholders $47 in Northrop common stock for each share of TRW, an 18 percent premium based on TRW's closing price of $39.80 on Thursday. Northrop would also assume about $5.5 billion in debt.
