aVThis was not how Philip A. Odeen expected 2002 to go. He had spent more than 40 years working his way up management ladders in government and the private sector. At 66 and newly retired as executive vice president for Washington operations for the TRW Corporation, he was ready for a new phase. He would still consult for TRW and the government, and he would still fulfill his duties as a director of four companies.
