VThe Northrop Grumman Corporation, the nation's third-largest military contractor, agreed to buy TRW Inc. for $7.8 billion in stock yesterday, in a deal that will make Northrop almost as large as the Lockheed Martin Corporation and the Boeing Company. The TRW deal, which will give Northrop the power to compete more effectively for new federal contracts for domestic security and space electronics, caps a string of acquisitions for the company, which is based in Los Angeles. Five years ago, antitrust concerns halted a plan by Lockheed to take over Northrop, forcing Northrop to embark on a new strategic direction to grow by takeovers.
