VThe New York Stock Exchange reported yesterday that short interest rose 24.6 million shares, or 8.4 percent, in the month ended March 14, to a record 318.6 million shares. The previous high of 301.9 million shares was set Dec. 13, 1985. In the same period, the short interest on the American Stock Exchange was down 536,239 shares, to 24.8 million shares. The following Big Board companies show large changes:
