VThe proposed merger of Lockheed Martin and Northrop Grumman is unlikely to face a serious regulatory challenge, experts said today, because of a Clinton Administration policy of explicitly supporting the consolidation of military suppliers. Because companies that do business with the Pentagon have been encouraged to find merger partners to reduce overlap and overhead as the military contracting pie shrinks, an effort to block the deal would represent a major change in policy.
