VThe trustees of the Grumman Corporation employee stock fund, which controls a third of the company, have decided to sell the stock to the Northrop Corporation as part of Northrop's $2.17 billion takeover offer. With the largest single block of stock, Grumman employees figured prominently in the takeover. The trustees said the stock would be transferred on Friday, the deadline for Northrop's offer of $62 a share. The Martin Marietta Corporation, the only other bidder for Grumman, has dropped out of the running and allowed its $55-a-share offer to expire. At $62 a share, the Grumman employee fund is worth $696.2 million, 55 percent more than it was worth on the day before Martin Marietta announced its bid.
