aVDefense Secretary Dick Cheney's decision on Monday to cancel the A-12 attack aircraft comes when the airplane's builders, the McDonnell Douglas Corporation and the General Dynamics Corporation, are facing steady declines in most of their other large Pentagon projects. Because the $57 billion program is the largest military program ever to be terminated by the Pentagon, the decision also makes the companies the clearest victims yet within the arms-building business of Federal budget pressures and the continuing decline in the size of the nation's military force.
