aVNewport News Shipbuilding Inc., the nation's only builder of nuclear aircraft carriers, became part of the Northrop Grumman Corporation yesterday. Northrop, the military conglomerate based in Los Angeles, took possession of Newport, its third shipyard, a little more than three weeks after the Newport board agreed to the $2.1 billion takeover. Northrop also owns the Avondale and Ingalls shipyards in Louisiana and Mississippi and is now the world's largest naval shipbuilder, Kent Kresa, Northrop's chief executive, said. The company is also the nation's third-largest military contractor, he said, with nearly 100,000 employees and expected 2002 revenues of $18 billion.
