aVTHE news on the job front has not been good. Employers have cut hundreds of thousands of positions this year in response to the weakening economy, especially after Sept. 11, and there are more reports of corporate retrenchment almost every day. The unemployment rate has risen to 5.4 percent, near a five-year high, and is poised to grow. But that does not mean jobs are impossible to find; you just have to know where to look. Several industries seem immune to the current economic downturn, including health care and pharmaceuticals, education, mortgage banking and security. Many employers in those sectors are regularly adding to their work force, economists say.
